item.title: OLD FILES ON THE RS JAGGRAB SERVER!: false alarm
item.dc:creator: @Killer-99-pkz Killer-99-pkz
item.description:
@Killer-99-pkz wrote:

I was implementing jaggrab to my version tracker and i requested a file from 553!!

i requested “runescape_411728210.pack200” which is from an older client, 553. and it still works!

	public static byte[] getjag(String s, String s1)
	{
		try
		{
			Socket s = new Socket();
			s.connect(new InetSocketAddress(InetAddress.getByName(s), 443), 0);
			s.setSoTimeout(30000);
			OutputStream t = s.getOutputStream();
			t.write(17);
			t.write(("JAGGRAB /" + s1 + "\n\n").getBytes());
			InputStream n = s.getInputStream();
			ByteArrayOutputStream b = new ByteArrayOutputStream();
			byte[] y = new byte[1000];
			for (int n = n.read(y, 0, 1000); n > 0; n = n.read(y, 0, 1000))
				b.write(y, 0, n);

			return b.toByteArray();
		}
		catch (IOException x)
		{
			return null;
		}
	}

EDIT: DAMN i just downloaded one of them for a test and it didint match the sha sum… boooooooo i think they just use the prefix “runescape” and for all the other files to for defining the file requested…
